      "id": "q2",
      "question": "Define BPE?",
      "answer": "Byte-Pair Encoding (BPE) is the dominant tokenization algorithm in modern Large Language Models (LLMs). Originally a data compression algorithm (by Gage in 1994), it was adapted for Natural Language Processing by Sennrich et al. in 2016. The tokenizer is trained separately on your text corpus before model training begins. It starts with a base vocabulary of individual units (characters or bytes) and merges the most frequent adjacent token pairs into new tokens until the target vocabulary size is reached. At inference, the same merge rules are applied to tokenize any new text in order to maintain consistency throughout all phases of processing.",
