      "id": "q5",
      "question": "Explain DAPO's Four Fixes.",
      "answer": "DAPO's Four Fixes are:\n1. Clip-Higher (Decoupled Clipping): use asymmetric clip bounds to increase exploration while maintaining stability.\n2. Dynamic Sampling: skip groups with identical rewards and oversample prompts to ensure a batch of informative groups.\n3. Token-Level Loss: normalize across all tokens in the batch equally to remove length bias, especially important for long Chain-of-Thought responses.\n4. Overlong Reward Shaping: mask truncated responses from loss entirely (to avoid noise) and add a linear soft length penalty as responses approach maximum length.",
